comment: Sample: BOVPN tunnel 'tunnel.2' local 172.16.12.81/255.255.255.255 remote 172.16.13.204/255.255.255.255 under gateway 'gateway.1' is down
Description: The status of the IPSec tunnel changed to up or down.
Format: %s tunnel '%s' local %s remote %s under gateway '%s' is %s
Variables: ${tunnel_type} tunnel '${tunnel}' local ${local} remote ${remote} under gateway '$(gateway}' is ${status}
Sample: The default IPSec certificate is not installed on the device
Description: The IPSec tunnel could not be negotiated because the default IPSec certificate is not installed or is not valid.
Format: The default IPSec certificate is not installed on the device
Sample: Could not read [DSA | RSA] certificate with [n] ID
Description: The IPSec tunnel could not be negotiated because the IPSec certificate is not valid.
Format: Could not read %s certificate with %d ID
Variables: Could not read ${cert_type} certificate with ${id} ID
Sample: Virtual IP address from 'abcd' address pool is not available for Mobile VPN with IPSec user 'Bob'
Description: All virtual IP addresses allocated to this Mobile VPN with IPSec group are already assigned. New Mobile VPN with IPSec tunnels cannot be established unless existing tunnels are deleted.
Format: Virtual IP address from '%s' address pool is not available for Mobile VPN with IPSec user '%s'
Variables: Virtual IP address from ${pool_name} address pool is not available for Mobile VPN with IPSec user ${user}
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received 'Aggressive mode' exchange type. Expecting main mode.
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of incorrect exchange type in proposal from remote gateway. The log message specifies the expected and received exchange type.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Received '%s' exchange type. Expecting main mode.
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Received '${exchange_type}' exchange type. Expecting main mode.
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received 'Main mode' exchange type. Expecting aggressive mode.
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of incorrect exchange type in proposal from remote gateway. The log message specifies the expected and received exchange type.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Received '%s' exchange type. Expecting aggressive mode.
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Received '${exchange_type}' exchange type. Expecting aggressive mode.
Sample: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received DH group 2, expecting 14"
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of incorrect Diffe-Hellman group in proposal from remote gateway. The log message specifies the received and expected group number.
Format: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Received DH group %d, expecting %d"
Variables: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Received DH group ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received hash SHA1, expecting MD5"
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of incorrect hash type in proposal from remote gateway. The log message specifies the received and expected hash type.
Format: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Received hash %s, expecting %s"
Variables: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Received hash ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received encryption 3DES, expecting AES"
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of incorrect encryption type in proposal from remote gateway. The log message specifies the received and expected encryption type.
Format: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Received encryption %s, expecting %s"
Variables: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Received encryption ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received authentication method PSK, expecting RSA certificate"
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of incorrect authentication method in proposal from remote gateway. The log message specifies the received and expected authentication methods.
Format: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Received authentication method %s, expecting %s"
Variables: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Received authentication method ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received AES key length 128, expecting 256"
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of incorrect AES key length in proposal from remote gateway. The log message specifies the received and expected AES key length.
Format: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Received AES key length %d, expecting %d"
Variables: "IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Received AES key length ${received}, expecting ${expected}"

Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received invalid main/aggressive mode first message. Check VPN IKE diagnostic log messages for more information.
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of invalid first message received by local gateway. The log message specifies the reason.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Received invalid main/aggressive mode first message. Check VPN IKE diagnostic log messages for more information.

Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Received invalid main/aggressive mode first message. Check VPN IKE diagnostic log messages for more information.
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Reason=Main mode matching policy not found
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation because local gateway did not find a matching Aggressive mode policy.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Reason=Main mode matching policy not found
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Reason=Main mode matching policy not found
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Authentication failure due to mismatched ID setting
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because remote ID in gateway configuration did not match proposal from remote gateway.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Authentication failure due to mismatched ID setting
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Authentication failure due to mismatched ID setting
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Pre-shared key authentication failure
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because pre-shared key in proposal did not match gateway configuration.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Pre-shared key authentication failure
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Pre-shared key authentication failure
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 2.2.2.2:500 to 1.1.1.1:500 failed. Reason=Received invalid message
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of the reason specified in the log
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s:%d to %s:%d failed. Reason=%s
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${src}:${sport} to ${dst}:${dport} failed - ${reason}
Sample: Received 'Invalid Exchange Type' message from 172.16.12.81:500 for 'gateway.1' gateway endpoint. Check VPN IKE diagnostic log messages on the remote gateway endpoint for more information.
Description: Received the specified information or error message from remote gateway.
Format: Received '%s' message from %s for '%s' gateway endpoint. Check VPN IKE diagnostic log messages on the remote gateway endpoint for more information.
Variables: Received '${info_msg}' message from ${peer_addr} for '${gw-ep}' gateway endpoint. Check VPN IKE diagnostic log messages on the remote gateway endpoint for more information.

Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.81:500 to 172.16.12.82:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Message retry timeout. Check the connection between local and remote gateway endpoints.
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of no response from remote site.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Message retry timeout. Check the connection between local and remote gateway endpoints.

Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Message retry timeout. Check the connection between local and remote gateway endpoints.
Sample: Rejected MUVPN IPSec user from 2.2.2.2 because maximum allowed user connections has been reached. Maximum:50

Description: Specified Mobile VPN with IPSec user connection rejected because the specified concurrent user connections limit has been reached. The log message specifies the concurrent user connections limit.
Format: Rejected MUVPN IPSec user from %s because maximum allowed user connections has been reached. Maximum:%d
Variables: Rejected MUVPN IPSec user from ${peer_addr} because maximum allowed user connections has been reached. Maximum:${max_value}
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=No CA certificate available
Description: IKE phase-1 negotiation failed because no Certificate Authority (CA) certificate is available.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=%s
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=${reason}
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=No CA certificate available
Description: IKE phase-1 negotiation failed because no Certificate Authority (CA) certificate is available.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=%s
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=${reason}
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Peer certificate is not issued by known trusted CA
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because peer certificate is not issued by a known and trusted Certificate Authority(CA).
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=%s
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=${reason}
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received certificate with invalid CA name
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of invalid Certificate Authority (CA) name in certificate for remote gateway.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=%s
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=${reason}
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Message decryption failed due to possible shared secret mismatch
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of possible shared key mismatch.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Message decryption failed due to possible shared secret mismatch
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Message decryption failed due to possible shared secret mismatch
Sample: Remote gateway 'gateway.1' with IP 172.16.13.204:500 did not send DPD R_U_THERE_ACK message. 2 retries left

Description: "Firebox or XTM device sent a DPD_R_U_THERE request to remote gateway, but did not receive DPD R_U_THERE_ACK response. The log message specifies the number of retries before it will delete the VPN tunnel."
Format: Remote gateway '%s' with IP %s did not send DPD R_U_THERE_ACK message. %d retries left
Variables: Remote gateway '${gw-ep}' with IP ${peer_addr} did not send DPD R_U_THERE_ACK message. ${n} retries left.

Sample: Remote gateway 'gateway.1' with IP 172.16.13.204:500 presumed dead due to DPD failure. Deleted all tunnels that use this gateway. Check the connection between local and remote gateway endpoints.
Description: The Firebox or XTM device deleted a VPN tunnel because the remote gateway did not respond to DPD R_U_THERE requests.
Format: Remote gateway '%s' with IP %s presumed dead due to DPD failure.%s
Variables: Remote gateway '${gw-ep}' with IP ${peer_addr} presumed dead due to DPD failure. ${action}
Sample: Remote gateway 'gateway.1' with IP 172.16.13.204:500 did not send KEEP_ALIVE_ACK message. 2 retries left.

Description: "Firebox or XTM device sent a KEEP_ALIVE request to remote gateway, but did not receive KEEP_ALIVE_ACK response. The log message specifies the number of retries before it will delete the VPN tunnel."
Format: Remote gateway '%s' with IP %s did not send KEEP_ALIVE_ACK message. %d retries left.
Variables: Remote gateway '${gw-ep}' with IP ${peer_addr} did not send KEEP_ALIVE_ACK message. ${n} retries left.

Sample: Remote gateway 'gateway.1' with IP 172.16.13.204:500 presumed dead due to keep-alive negotiation failure. Deleted all tunnels that use this gateway. Check the connection between local and remote gateway endpoints.
Description: Firebox or XTM device deleted one or more VPN tunnels because the remote gateway did not respond to keep-alive requests.
Format: Remote gateway '%s' with IP %s presumed dead due to keep-alive negotiation failure.%s
Variables: Remote gateway '${gw-ep}' with IP ${peer_addr} presumed dead due to keep-alive negotiation failure.${action}
Sample: Received IKE message from 172.16.13.204:500 for unknown P1 SA. Sending delete message to remote gateway 'gateway.1'.
Description: Received IKE message for unknown P1 SA. Sending delete message to remote gateway
Format: Received IKE message from %s for unknown P1 SA. Sending delete message to remote gateway '%s'.
Variables: Received IKE message from ${peer_addr} for unknown P1 SA. Sending delete message to remote gateway '${gateway}'.
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Authentication failure due to mismatched DSS certificate ID setting
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of mismatched DSS certificate ID setting.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Authentication failure due to mismatched DSS certificate ID setting
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Authentication failure due to mismatched DSS certificate ID setting
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Failed to get ID information from certificate 20001
Description: IKE phase-1 negotiation failed because failed to get ID information from certificate.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Failed to get ID information from certificate %d
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Failed to get ID information from certificate ${certificate_id}
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 198.51.100.2:500 to 203.0.113.2:500 failed. Reason=Received IKE message on wrong interface 'eth0'(index:3). Expecting it to be received on 'eth6'.
Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because of IKE message peer was received on wrong interface.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Reason=Received IKE message on wrong interface '%s'(index:%d). Expecting it to be received on '%s'.

Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Reason=Received IKE message on wrong interface '${received_if}'(index:${received_ifindex}). Expecting it to be received on '${expected_if}'
Sample: IKE phase-1 negotiation from 198.51.100.2:500 to 203.0.113.2:500 failed. Gateway-Endpoint='gateway.1' Reason=Received ID did not match with configured aggressive mode ID.

Description: IKE Phase 1 negotiation failed because received ID did not match with configured ID on local gateway. Check aggressive mode ID information in gateway endpoint configuration on both local and remote gateways.
Format: IKE phase-1 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Gateway-Endpoint='%s' Reason=Received ID did not match with configured aggressive mode ID.
Variables: IKE phase-1 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Gateway-Endpoint='${gw-ep}' Reason=Received ID did not match with configured aggressive mode ID.
Sample: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Tunnel='tunnel.1' Reason=Received proposal without PFS, Expecting PFS enabled"
Description: The IPSec tunnel negotiation failed because the Perfect Forward Secrecy (PFS) value did not match the Phase 2 configuration.
Format: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Tunnel='%s' Reason=Received proposal without PFS, Expecting PFS enabled"
Variables: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Tunnel='${tunnel}' Reason=Received proposal without PFS, Expecting PFS enabled"
Sample: IKE phase-2 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Tunnel='tunnel.1' Reason=Received protocol 'AH'. Expecting 'ESP' in phase-2 proposal.
Description: The IPSec tunnel negotiation failed because the proposal did not match the Phase 2 configuration. The log message specifies the received and expected proposals.
Format: IKE phase-2 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Tunnel='%s' Reason=Received protocol '%s'. Expecting '%s' in phase-2 proposal.
Variables: IKE phase-2 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Tunnel='${tunnel}' Reason=Received protocol '${received_proto}'. Expecting '${expected_proto}' in phase-2 proposal.
Sample: IKE phase-2 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Tunnel='tunnel.1' Reason=Received protocol 'AH'. Expecting 'ESP' in phase-2 proposal.
Description: The IPSec tunnel negotiation failed because the proposal did not match the Phase 2 configuration. The log message specifies the received and expected proposals.
Format: IKE phase-2 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Tunnel='%s' Reason=Received protocol '%s'. Expecting '%s' in phase-2 proposal.
Variables: IKE phase-2 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Tunnel='${tunnel}' Reason=Received protocol '${received_proto}'. Expecting '${expected_proto}' in phase-2 proposal.
Sample: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Tunnel='tunnel.1' Reason=Received AH authentication MD5, expecting SHA1"

Description: The IPSec tunnel negotiation failed because the proposed AH authentication method did not match the Phase 2 configuration. The log message specifies the received and expected AH authentication method.
Format: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Tunnel='%s' Reason=Received AH authentication %s, expecting %s"
Variables: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Tunnel='${tunnel}' Reason=Received AH authentication ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Tunnel='tunnel.1' Reason=Received ESP encryption DES, expecting AES"

Description: The IPSec tunnel negotiation failed because the proposed ESP encryption method did not match the Phase 2 configuration. The log message specifies the received and expected ESP encryption method.
Format: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Tunnel='%s' Reason=Received ESP encryption %s, expecting %s"
Variables: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Tunnel='${tunnel}' Reason=Received ESP encryption ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Tunnel='tunnel.1' Reason=Received PFS DH group 2, expecting 5"

Description: The IPSec tunnel negotiation failed because the proposed Perfect Forward Secrecy Diffe-Hellman (PFS DH) group number did not match the Phase 2 configuration. The log message specifies the received and expected PFS DH group numbers.
Format: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Tunnel='%s' Reason=Received PFS DH group %d, expecting %d"
Variables: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Tunnel='${tunnel}' Reason=Received PFS DH group ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Tunnel='tunnel.1' Reason=Received ESP authentication MD5-HMAC, expecting SHA1-HMAC"

Description: The IPSec tunnel negotiation failed because the proposed ESP authentication method did not match the Phase 2 configuration. The log message specifies the received and expected ESP authentication method.
Format: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Tunnel='%s' Reason=Received ESP authentication %s, expecting %s"
Variables: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Tunnel='${tunnel}' Reason=Received ESP authentication ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Tunnel='tunnel.1' Reason=Received AES key length 128, expecting 256"

Description: The IPSec tunnel negotiation failed because the proposed AES encryption key length did not match the Phase 2 configuration. The log message specifies the received and expected AES key length.
Format: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Tunnel='%s' Reason=Received AES key length %d, expecting %d"
Variables: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Tunnel='${tunnel}' Reason=Received AES key length ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from 172.16.12.82:500 to 172.16.12.81:500 failed. Tunnel='tunnel.1' Reason=Received AES key length 128, expecting 256"

Description: The IPSec tunnel negotiation failed because the proposed AES encryption key length did not match the Phase 2 configuration. The log message specifies the received and expected AES key length.
Format: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from %s to %s failed. Tunnel='%s' Reason=Received AES key length %d, expecting %d"
Variables: "IKE phase-2 negotiation from ${local_addr} to ${peer_addr} failed. Tunnel='${tunnel}' Reason=Received AES key length ${received}, expecting ${expected}"
Sample: Received 'No Proposal Chosen' message from 172.16.12.81:500 for 'tunnel.1' tunnel. Check VPN IKE diagnostic log messages on the remote gateway endpoint for more information.
Description: Remote gateway sent an information error message in response to VPN tunnel proposal.
Format: Received '%s' message from %s for '%s' tunnel. Check VPN IKE diagnostic log messages on the remote gateway endpoint for more information.
Variables: Received '${info_msg}' message from ${peer_addr} for '${tunnel}' tunnel. Check VPN IKE diagnostic log messages on the remote gateway endpoint for more information.
Sample: Dropped a simultaneous phase-2 negotiation from the peer 172.16.13.204:500
Description: Firebox or XTM device dropped phase-2 negotiation because of another Phase 2 negotiation in progress.
Format: Dropped a simultaneous phase-2 negotiation from the peer %s
Variables: Dropped a simultaneous IPSec negotiation from the peer ${peer_addr}
Sample: Received XAuth failed notification from 172.16.24.1:4500. Group:'ToFirebox_mu'
Description: Received notification that Extended Authentication(XAuth) failed. Aborting XAuth negotiation.
Format: Received XAuth failed notification from %s. Group:'%s'
Variables: Received XAuth failed notification from ${peer_addr}. Group:'${gateway}'

Description: Rejected proposed Phase 1 authentication method because Firebox or XTM Device expects client Extended Authentication(XAuth) enabled.
Format: "Rejected phase-1 authentication method %s from %s, expecting client XAUTH enabled."
Variables: "Rejected phase 1 authentication method ${auth_method} from ${peer_addr}, expecting client XAUTH enabled."
Sample: "Rejected phase-1 authentication method PSK from 172.16.24.1:4500, expecting server XAUTH enabled."
Description: Rejected proposed Phase 1 authentication method because Firebox or XTM Device expects server Extended Authentication(XAuth) enabled.
Format: "Rejected phase-1 authentication method %s from %s, expecting server XAUTH enabled."
Variables: "Rejected phase 1 authentication method ${auth_method} from ${peer_addr}, expecting server XAUTH enabled."
Sample: XAuth negotiation from 172.16.24.1:4500 failed due to a mismatched XAuthMode.

Format: XAuth negotiation from %s failed due to a mismatched XAuthMode.
Variables: XAuth negotiation from ${peer_addr} failed due to a mismatched XAuthMode
Sample: MUVPN user authentication failed due to unresponsive peer at 172.16.24.1:4500
Description: Mobile VPN with IPSec user authentication failed because the peer did not respond.

Variables: MUVPN user authentication failed due to unresponsive peer at %s

Variables: MUVPN user '${user_name}' is authenticated without group information

Variables: ${vpn_user_type} ${user_name} logged in. Virtual IP address is ${virtual_ipaddr}. Real IP address is ${real_ipaddr}.
Sample: Mobile VPN with SSL user tsmith logged off. Virtual IP address is 192.168.113.2.
Description: The VPN with SSL user with the specified virtual IP address logged out.
Format: %s %s logged off. Virtual IP address is %s.
Variables: ${vpn_user_type} ${user_name} logged off. Virtual IP address was ${virtual_ipaddr}.
Sample: The IPSec IKE process started.
Description: WatchGuard iked v11.6.B341909 (C) 1996-2012 WatchGuard Technologies Inc. starts at Wed Jun 30 21:49:08 2012
Format: WatchGuard iked v%s %s starts at %s
Sample: An IPSec configuration update started.
Description: Started processing a configuration setting
Format: Started to process a configuration setting
Sample: An IPSec configuration update was successfully completed.
Description: A configuration setting has been processed successfully
Format: A configuration setting has been processed successfully
Sample: The device is not activated. IPSec tunnels cannot be established.
Description: "WARNING! Tunnel negotiation is NOT allowed because the local box is not activated yet(no "LIVESECURITY" feature key is found)!!"
Format: "WARNING! Tunnel negotiation is NOT allowed because the local box is not activated yet(no "LIVESECURITY" feature key is found)!!"
Sample: The IPSec tunnel was established or re-keyed successfully. The log message includes the security association identifiers.
Description: 'gateway.1' BOVPN IPSec tunnel is established. local:192.168.81.0/28 remote:192.168.25.0/28 in-SA:0x445e72b7 out-SA:0x5f9f256f role:responder
Format: '%s' %s IPSec tunnel is %s. local:%s remote:%s in-SA:0x%08x out-SA:0x%08x role:%s
Variables: ${gateway} ${tunnel_type} IPSec tunnel is ${action}. local:${local} remote:${remote} in-spi:${in_spi} out-spi:${out_spi} role:${nego_role}
Sample: The maximum allowed number of BOVPN tunnel routes have been established. No new tunnel routes can be created until active tunnel routes expire or are deleted.
Description: The maximum number of allowed active BOVPN tunnels has been reached (Maximum: 500 Current: 500).
Format: The maximum number of active allowed BOVPN tunnels has been reached (Maximum: %d Current: %d)
Sample: The maximum allowed number of BOVPN tunnel routes have been established. No new tunnel routes can be created until active tunnel routes expire or are deleted.
Description: The maximum number of allowed active BOVPN tunnels has been reached (Maximum: 500 Current: 500).
Format: The maximum number of active allowed BOVPN tunnels has been reached (Maximum: %d Current: %d)
Sample: The cluster master has changed because of a FireCluster failover. The local device will not handle IKE negotiation.
Description: A FireCluster failover occurred. The cluster master has changed.
Format: A FireCluster failover occurred. The cluster master has changed.
Sample: The Mobile VPN with L2TP daemon started.
Description: The Mobile VPN with L2TP daemon started successfully.
Format: The Mobile VPN with L2TP daemon started successfully.
Sample: The Mobile VPN with L2TP daemon received a configuration update.
Description: Updating configuration for Mobile VPN with L2TP.
Format: Updating configuration for Mobile VPN with L2TP.
Sample: The Mobile VPN with L2TP daemon stopped.
Description: Stopped Mobile VPN with L2TP daemon.
Format: Stopped Mobile VPN with L2TP daemon.
